[This is a very clear & basically accurate description of the disease, its
history & control. I would only comment that "the so-called viral
haemorrhagic fevers group" is not a taxonomically homogeneous group, merely
a symptomatic one, which also includes yellow fever. The filoviruses
Marburg & Ebola form a family quite distinct from the other viruses
mentioned, which in turn belong to several disparate taxonomic groups. By
"manipulation of the bodies" of people or animals dead from possible
Marburg virus infection is meant the removal of viscera, which risks
contaminating
the hands of the manipulator with infected blood. - Mod. JW
.......................jw/ds
